---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import CtaBand from '../components/CtaBand.astro';
import { Phone, ArrowUpRight } from '@lucide/astro';
import FacebookIcon from '../components/FacebookIcon.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';

const lastUpdated = 'May 2026';
---
<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy - Jack's Garage | Classic VW Specialists London W10"
  description="How Jack's Garage in Ladbroke Grove, London W10 collects, uses and protects your personal data under UK GDPR, and how to exercise your data rights."
  path="/privacy-policy"
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Privacy Policy"
    subtitle="How Jack's Garage handles your personal data."
    breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'Privacy Policy' }]}
  >
    <a href={site.phone.href} class="btn btn-primary btn-lg"><Phone size={18} /> {site.phone.display}</a>
    <a href="/contact-us" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg">Contact us <ArrowUpRight size={16} class="arrow" /></a>
  </PageHero>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-jg">
      <div class="prose-jg mx-auto max-w-3xl">
        <p class="reveal text-muted">
          This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Jack's Garage</strong> ("we", "us", "our") collects, uses and
          protects the personal data you share with us, and the rights you have under the UK General Data Protection
          Regulation (UK GDPR) and the Data Protection Act 2018. We are committed to keeping the limited information
          we hold about you safe and to being clear about how we use it.
        </p>

        <h2 class="reveal">Who we are</h2>
        <p>
          Jack's Garage is a family-run Classic VW specialist based in Ladbroke Grove, West London. For the purposes
          of UK data protection law, we are the <strong>data controller</strong> responsible for your personal data.
          You can reach us at:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Jack's Garage</strong></li>
          <li>{site.address.line1}, {site.address.city} {site.address.postcode}</li>
          <li>Telephone: <a href={site.phone.href}>{site.phone.display}</a> (Monday to Friday, 8am to 6pm)</li>
          <li>Facebook: <a href={site.facebook} target="_blank" rel="noopener">facebook.com/JacksGarageW10</a></li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not operate a public email address. The quickest way to reach us is by phone, through our on-site
          enquiry forms, or via our Facebook page.
        </p>

        <h2 class="reveal">What information we collect</h2>
        <p>
          We only collect the information we genuinely need to answer your enquiry and to look after your vehicle.
          Depending on how you contact us, this may include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Information you give us through an enquiry or contact form</strong> - your name, email address,
            telephone number, vehicle details (such as registration, make and model) and the content of any message
            you send us.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Information you give us by phone, in person or on Facebook</strong> - the details you choose to
            share with us so that we can advise you, provide a quote or carry out work on your vehicle.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Technical and cookie data</strong> - basic information collected automatically when you browse
            this website, such as your IP address, browser type and how you use the site. For more on this, please
            see our <a href="/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a>.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not knowingly collect any special category data and we ask that you do not send us sensitive personal
          information through our forms.
        </p>

        <h2 class="reveal">How we use your information and our lawful bases</h2>
        <p>
          We use your personal data only for clear and limited purposes, and always rely on a lawful basis under the
          UK GDPR:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>To respond to your enquiry</strong> and provide you with information, advice or a quote. When you
            submit an enquiry form, we rely on your <strong>consent</strong>, which you give by ticking the consent
            box, and on our <strong>legitimate interests</strong> in answering your message.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>To provide our services</strong> - booking your vehicle in, carrying out servicing, MOTs,
            bodywork, repairs or EV conversions, and keeping you updated on the work. Where you become a customer,
            we rely on the <strong>performance of a contract</strong> with you and on our legitimate interests in
            running the workshop.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>To keep proper business records</strong> and meet our legal and accounting obligations, where we
            rely on <strong>compliance with a legal obligation</strong>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>To maintain and secure this website</strong>, where we rely on our legitimate interests in
            keeping the site working safely and reliably.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not use your details to send marketing unless you have specifically asked us to, and we will never
          sell your information.
        </p>

        <h2 class="reveal">Sharing your information</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell, rent or trade your personal data, and we keep the people who can see it to a minimum. We
          will only share your information where it is necessary to do so, for example with:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            trusted parts suppliers, specialist sub-contractors or our EV conversion partner where this is needed to
            carry out work on your vehicle;
          </li>
          <li>
            your insurer or a third party you have asked us to deal with on your behalf, for example in connection
            with a bodywork or accident repair;
          </li>
          <li>
            our professional advisers (such as our accountants) and service providers who help us run the workshop
            and this website;
          </li>
          <li>
            law enforcement, regulators or other authorities where we are required to do so by law.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Where we use other organisations to process data on our behalf, we put appropriate safeguards in place and
          they may only use your data on our instructions.
        </p>

        <h2 class="reveal">How long we keep your information</h2>
        <p>
          We keep your personal data only for as long as is necessary for the purposes set out in this policy. If you
          make an enquiry but do not go on to become a customer, we will normally delete your details once your
          enquiry has been dealt with. Where you become a customer, we keep service and vehicle records for as long
          as we reasonably need them to look after your VW and to meet our legal, accounting and tax obligations,
          after which they are securely deleted or anonymised.
        </p>

        <h2 class="reveal">Your rights under UK GDPR</h2>
        <p>
          Under UK data protection law you have a number of rights over your personal data. These include the right
          to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Access</strong> the personal data we hold about you;</li>
          <li><strong>Rectification</strong> - to ask us to correct inaccurate or incomplete data;</li>
          <li><strong>Erasure</strong> - to ask us to delete your data in certain circumstances;</li>
          <li><strong>Restriction</strong> - to ask us to limit how we use your data;</li>
          <li><strong>Object</strong> to our processing of your data where we rely on legitimate interests;</li>
          <li><strong>Data portability</strong> - to receive certain data in a portable format; and</li>
          <li><strong>Withdraw consent</strong> at any time where we are relying on your consent.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, please contact us by phone on
          <a href={site.phone.href}>{site.phone.display}</a> or through our
          <a href="/contact-us">contact page</a>. We will respond within the timescales required by law.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you are unhappy with how we have handled your personal data, we would always like the chance to put
          things right, so please get in touch first. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the UK's
          supervisory authority, the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO), at
          <a href="https://ico.org.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ico.org.uk</a>.
        </p>

        <h2 class="reveal">Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          This website uses a small number of cookies and similar technologies to help it work properly and to
          understand how visitors use it. You can control or disable cookies through your browser settings. For full
          details of the cookies we use and how to manage them, please see our
          <a href="/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a>.
        </p>

        <h2 class="reveal">Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or in the law. Any
          changes will be published on this page, and we encourage you to review it occasionally. The date below
          shows when this policy was last updated.
        </p>

        <h2 class="reveal">How to contact us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or about how we handle your personal data, please
          contact us:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>By phone on <a href={site.phone.href}>{site.phone.display}</a> (Monday to Friday, 8am to 6pm);</li>
          <li>By message on <a href={site.facebook} target="_blank" rel="noopener">our Facebook page</a>; or</li>
          <li>Through our <a href="/contact-us">contact form</a>.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          You can also write to us at Jack's Garage, {site.address.line1}, {site.address.city} {site.address.postcode}.
        </p>

        <div class="reveal mt-12 flex flex-col gap-4 rounded-3xl border border-line bg-cream-200 p-6 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between">
          <p class="m-0 text-sm text-muted">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
            <a href={site.phone.href} class="btn btn-primary"><Phone size={17} /> Call the workshop</a>
            <a href={site.facebook} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-outline"><FacebookIcon size={16} /> Facebook</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CtaBand
    title="Questions about your data, or your VW?"
    subtitle="We keep things simple and honest. Call the team or send an enquiry and we'll be glad to help."
  />
</Layout>
